1156
01:09:14.050 --> 01:09:17.750
And the attraction for pharmaceutical companies to go into this

1157
01:09:17.830 --> 01:09:21.250
area is even harder. How do we really

1158
01:09:21.971 --> 01:09:23.210
make this more

1159
01:09:24.370 --> 01:09:27.869
tractable? That more will invest in monies and funding and

1160
01:09:28.391 --> 01:09:32.250
attracting more research into this space, which is everything you've told

1161
01:09:32.290 --> 01:09:36.110
me to date. I feel like we should start thinking more about it tomorrow, or

1162
01:09:36.190 --> 01:09:39.891
today even, and yet it's so hard to implement these areas of

1163
01:09:39.910 --> 01:09:40.471
research.

1164
01:09:42.630 --> 01:09:44.870
Good question. I can start.

1165
01:09:45.710 --> 01:09:49.530
Clearly, I think all of the funding for the last two or three

1166
01:09:49.610 --> 01:09:53.490
decades has really been focused on treatment because that's the patient

1167
01:09:53.590 --> 01:09:57.410
you get in the clinic, and they're in dire need of something to overcome the

1168
01:09:57.450 --> 01:10:01.210
disease. But if you look at statistics and populations,

1169
01:10:01.750 --> 01:10:05.240
clearly we can have a rapid impact in

1170
01:10:05.690 --> 01:10:09.490
prevention and early detection compared to getting

1171
01:10:09.499 --> 01:10:12.450
those successful treatments and cures on board.

1172
01:10:12.480 --> 01:10:16.450
And there's no reason why we can't do both, but my feeling is that

1173
01:10:16.530 --> 01:10:19.530
we have been underfunding the prevention side of things.

1174
01:10:20.050 --> 01:10:22.930
So I welcome anybody to make comments.

1175
01:10:24.850 --> 01:10:28.730
Can I say, one in 25 of the people who got aspirin in the CAP2 trial

